item.title: What to do forgot
item.dc:creator: @patargangstar patargangstar
item.description:
@patargangstar wrote:

[quote=“ApocalypseX, post:2, topic:398471”][quote author=XD you k0 XD link=topic=495607.msg3623375#msg3623375 date=1307638717]
forgot what to change at client.java i know about the server = change to like:
server = fatalityx.no-ip.org
but i need to change something else right?
like server equals or something please can someone help im portforwarded yes just forgot how to do online with teamviewer (if possible)
Thanks.
[/quote]
First, if you’re using PI…
Then CTRL + F Server
and if you see something that you searched Server = “”
And has two quotations, that means it’s empty and you should type in your IP.
If not, and you leeched (or downloaded) someone elses client they probably set it as ‘localhost’ or ‘127.0.0.1’ so search for those.
Best of luck![/quote]

some are also set to 0.0.0.0 which is localhost too
